ngagement started as an act of =\r\ngiving becomes entangled with pride, self-worth, desire and attachment and =\r\nbecomes more about taking than giving. It becomes about oneself than giving=\r\n others.\n=A0\nTHIS in a nutshell is the problem with engaging with the world=\r\n. But the bottomline is this: If you have a lot of rinas to others, you can=\r\nnot make spiritual progress without engaging with others and somehow managi=\r\nng to pay off those rinas. So, somehow you have to learn giving others self=\r\nlessly, without making it about yourself in the end! In all your relationsh=\r\nips, watch out for this tendency to make it about yourself and about what y=\r\nou are getting and consciously and constantly focus on giving and on others=\r\n.\n=A0\n5. If one doesn&#39;t have strong rinas to one&#39;s family members, renounci=\r\nng them may not block one&#39;s spiritual progress. If one has strong rinas, it=\r\n may block.\n=A0\nStaying away from objects of this world that are known sour=\r\nces of attachment, desires, aversion, fears and pride, can be useful for a =\r\nwhile. But, in the long term, desires, aversion, fears and pride may not be=\r\n overcome just by avoidance, if there are strong rinas. If you are not Sidd=\r\nhartha, what worked for Siddhartha need not work for you.\n=A0\nThe key is to=\r\n learn to give without taking, or atleast, without focusing the mind on tak=\r\ning. We are on earth to give.\n=A0\n6. You don&#39;t feed a 5-day old baby with b=\r\nesan laddoo, though it may be very tasty and protein-rich. Until one is not=\r\n ready, one need not be rushed into spirituality. At the same time, don&#39;t l=\r\nook down upon them. Everyone will go through their spiritual evolution phas=\r\nes.\n=A0\nInstead of liberation, talk to them about doing the right thing - d=\r\nharma. Talk to them about love, caring and compassion and doing the right t=\r\nhing fearlessly.\n=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spiritual=\r\nity Res